 {"id":"bd-2nug","title":"P5.4: Create DependencyTree component for pack dependency visualization","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-19T21:14:29.596588490Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-19T21:18:13.356342780Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2nug","depends_on_id":"bd-1nc9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-19T21:14:56.988916096Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":31,"issue_id":"bd-2nug","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"## Task: Create DependencyTree component for pack dependencies

### What to Do

Create a specialized Tree component showing pack dependency relationships (which packs include/extend others).

### Use Case

Some packs extend others:
- `kubernetes_production` extends `kubernetes_base`
- `git_strict` extends `git_safety`
- User packs can include built-in packs

### Implementation

```rust
#[cfg(feature = "rich-output")]
pub struct DependencyTree {
    root_packs: Vec<String>,
    dependencies: HashMap<String, Vec<String>>,
}

impl DependencyTree {
    pub fn from_packs(packs: &[Pack]) -> Self {
        let mut deps = HashMap::new();
        for pack in packs {
            if let Some(extends) = &pack.extends {
                deps.entry(pack.name.clone())
                    .or_insert_with(Vec::new)
                    .extend(extends.clone());
            }
        }
        // ... build root packs (those not extended by anyone)
    }

    pub fn render(&self, theme: &Theme) -> String {
        use rich_rust::prelude::*;

        let mut tree = Tree::new("[bold]Pack Dependencies[/]");

        for root in &self.root_packs {
            self.add_pack_node(&mut tree, root, 0);
        }

        tree.to_string()
    }

    fn add_pack_node(&self, parent: &mut TreeNode, pack: &str, depth: usize) {
        let style = if depth == 0 { "bold cyan" } else { "cyan" };
        let node = parent.add(format!("[{}]{}[/]", style, pack));

        if let Some(deps) = self.dependencies.get(pack) {
            for dep in deps {
                node.add(format!("[dim]extends[/] [yellow]{}[/]", dep));
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### Output Example

```
Pack Dependencies
├── [cyan]kubernetes_production[/]
│   └── [dim]extends[/] [yellow]kubernetes_base[/]
├── [cyan]git_strict[/]
│   └── [dim]extends[/] [yellow]git_safety[/]
└── [cyan]my_custom_pack[/]
    ├── [dim]extends[/] [yellow]filesystem_critical[/]
    └── [dim]extends[/] [yellow]database_safety[/]
```

### Integration

Add to `dcg packs --deps` or `dcg packs --tree --show-deps`.

### Considerations

- Detect circular dependencies (error)
- Show transitive dependencies with different styling
- Could combine with pattern counts
